headline.main: GERARD SWOPE, 84, EX-G.E. HEAD, DIES; President 20 Years Began Work for Company at $1 a Day While M.I.T. Student BROADENED ITS OUTPUT Power Fields Had Been City Housing Chairman

snippet: Gerard Swope, former president of the General Electric  Company and onetime chairman of the New York City Housing Authority, died yesterday at his home, 161 East Seventy-ninth Street. He was 84 years old.
